ADAR 2-15 Stock.name: AR-15 ADAR 2-15 wooden stock
ADAR 2-15 Stock.description: A wooden SVD-style stock for ADAR 2-15 carbines.

A2 Buffertube.name: Colt Carbine buffer tube
A2 Buffertube.description: Colt Receiver Extension Buffer Tube, 4-position, Mil-Spec diameter will fit any AR-15-based carbine.

Hera Arms CQR Stock.name: AR-15 Hera Arms CQR pistol grip/buttstock
Hera Arms CQR Stock.description: Designed for the cilvilian market as well as for military use, to create one of the most rigid and compact Rifle Systems based on the widely available AR-15 platform. The CQR Riflestock is an easy to install replacement buttstock for Mil-Spec AR-15 Rifles using a Mil-Spec Carbine buffer tube.

M4A1 Standard Stock.name: High Standard M4SS Stock
M4A1 Standard Stock.description: The High Standard M4SS telescoping stock closely follows the classic M4A1 stock except for a few geometry details.

AR15 14.5\" Barrel.name: AR-15 5.56x45 370mm barrel
AR15 14.5\" Barrel.description: A 370mm barrel for AR-15 based weapons for 5.56x45 NATO ammo. Corresponds with standard service M4A1 barrel.

A2 Pistol Grip.name: AR-15 Colt A2 pistol grip
A2 Pistol Grip.description: The Colt A2 polymer pistol grip can be installed on any weapon compatible with AR-15 grips. Standard-issue for all AR-15-based weapons of US Army and USMC.

M4A1 Standard Handguard.name: AR-15 Colt M4 Carbine Length handguard
M4A1 Standard Handguard.description: A carbine length handguard manufactured by Colt, a standard-issue handguard for the M4A1 assault rifles.

AR15 Charging Handle.name: AR-15 Colt charging handle
AR15 Charging Handle.description: A standard charging handle for AR-15 and compatible systems, manufactured by Colt.

M4A1 Upper.name: M4A1 5.56x45 upper receiver
M4A1 Upper.description: An upper receiver for the M4A1 assault rifle manufactured by Colt. Equipped with a mount for attaching additional devices.

M4 Front Post Gas Block.name: M4A1 front sight with gas block
M4 Front Post Gas Block.description: A standard-issue front sight with gas block for M4A1 assault rifles, manufactured by Colt.

DingPack.name: Ding Pack
DingPack.description: Really just a pack of mini sausages. This world's equivalent of cigarettes. Seemingly the only brand available.

Matchbox.name: Matchbox
Matchbox.description: A matchbox full of safety matches. Lighters are more reliable and easier to use, but that's exactly why everybody tries to keep them hidden when asked for a light.

FlipzoLighter.name: Flipzo Lighter
FlipzoLighter.description: A metal gasoline Flipzo lighter, renowned for being reliable and windproof.

HairsprayCan.name: Hairspray Can
HairsprayCan.description: A generic can of hairspray. Kinda weird since sosigs don't have hair, but, well, they hold guns without arms either so I guess thats fine. We'll find some use for it.

Drill.name: Electric Drill
Drill.description: A cordless electric drill. Used in construction, furniture installation, and repair.

AK74N.name: Kalashnikov AK-74N 5.45x39 assault rifle
AK74N.description: The AK-74N is a Russian Assault Rifle that replaced the AKM as the main service rifle. It fires a smaller cartridge with flatter trajectory, but otherwise shares many of the same features as the AKM. The "N" in the name indicates that this rifle is fitted with a dovetail, which was the standard optical mounting system for Eastern Bloc weaponry.

545x39mmCartridgeFMJ.name: 5.45x39mm FMJ Round
545x39mmCartridgeFMJ.description: 5.45x39mm is an intermediate rifle cartridge. Full Metal Jacket.

UtilityFlashlight.name: Utility Flashlight
UtilityFlashlight.description: The Flashlight is a utility item for lighting up dark areas. The flashlight can be held by the player in their hand, or it can be used in a quickbelt slot to light the way ahead.

ModulM4A1.name: Colt M4A1 5.56x45 assault rifle
ModulM4A1.description:
The Colt M4A1 carbine is a fully automatic variant of the basic M4 Carbine and was primarily designed for special operations use.
However, U.S. Special Operations Command (USSOCOM) was soon to adopt the M4A1 for almost all special operations units, followed later by general introduction of the M4A1 into service with the U.S. Army and Marine Corps.

Sight_Rear_M4CarryHandle.name: AR-15 rear sight carry handle
Sight_Rear_M4CarryHandle.description: A detachable carry handle with a rear sight for AR-15 rifles. Standard-issue for M4A1 assault rifles.

MuzzleBrake_A2.name: AR-15 Colt USGI A2 5.56x45 flash hider
MuzzleBrake_A2.description: The 5.56x45 Colt USGI A2 flash hider (a.k.a. Bird Cage) is designed for mounting on 5.56x45 weapons built on the AR-15 system. However, it can be installed on other weapons of the same caliber provided that barrel has the same threading for muzzle devices. A service muzzle device for M4A1.
